    <Overview name="Overview0">
      <links/>
      <content><![CDATA[<p>In OpenCms contents are stored as XML files. Thus, the structure of a content of specific type, but also much of its behavior, is specified in an XML schema definition (XSD). Those XSDs themselves must comply to a special structure. In this topic you learn about the general structure of such schemas and learn how to create a new schema in OpenCms.</p>]]></content>
    </Overview>
    <Teaser name="Teaser0">
      <links/>
      <content><![CDATA[<p>For each content type the structure and content specific behavior is specified in XML schema defintions. Find out how to write such a defintion.</p>]]></content>
    </Teaser>
    <Keywords><![CDATA[content, XML, XSD, schema]]></Keywords>
